org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.io

Class TimestampLocalTZWritable

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.io.TimestampLocalTZWritable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<TimestampLocalTZWritable>, org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable, org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<TimestampLocalTZWritable>

    public class TimestampLocalTZWritable
extends Object
implements org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<TimestampLocalTZWritable>
    Writable for TimestampTZ. Copied from TimestampWritableV2. After we replace Timestamp with LocalDateTime for Timestamp, it'll need a new Writable. All timestamp with time zone will be serialized as UTC retaining the instant. E.g. "2017-04-14 18:00:00 Asia/Shanghai" will be converted to "2017-04-14 10:00:00.0 Z".
